"Joker" is "poker" with a "J"!

278
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,030
Coincidence?

279
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,520
That's "joincidence" with a "C"!

280
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,360
Look!

281
00:11:55,410 --> 00:11:57,700
Ugly Naked Guy lit a bunch of candles.

282
00:12:04,710 --> 00:12:06,530
That had to hurt!

283
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:11,650
Hey, it's your Thanksgiving too.

284
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,240
Instead of watching football,

285
00:12:13,290 --> 00:12:14,380
you could help.

286
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:15,570
We know.

287
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:19,300
Rachel, you want to put the marshmallows

288
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:20,500
in concentric circles.

289
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:21,470
No, Mon.

290
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,720
You want to put them in concentric circles.

291
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:25,700
I want to do this.

292
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:36,360
Every year.

293
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:41,610
It's stuck!

294
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:44,570
Step.

295
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:46,080
How did it get on?

296
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:48,880
I put it on to scare Chandler.

297
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:50,750
Oh, my God!

298
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,050
Monica's going to totally freak out!

299
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,290
Plus, it smells really bad in here.

300
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:56,930
Of course it smells bad.

301
00:12:56,980 --> 00:12:59,690
You have your head up a turkey's ass.

302
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:03,550
Monica.

303
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,620
Did you get the turkey--?

304
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:09,720
Oh, my God!

305
00:13:10,930 --> 00:13:12,130
Who is that?

306
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:13,720
It's Joey.

307
00:13:14,930 --> 00:13:15,870
I got it!

308
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,550
If we win,

309
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,230
they have to get rid of the rooster.

310
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,960
That's interesting!

311
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,840
If you win...

312
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:25,620
...we give up the bird.

313
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:29,930
But if we win...

314
00:13:31,030 --> 00:13:32,490
...we get your apartment.

315
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:37,490
- Deal! - What?

316
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,950
"What was Monica's nickname

317
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,670
when she was a hockey goalie?"

318
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,170
- Big Fat Goalie. - Correct!

319
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:47,380
"Rachel claims it's her favorite movie."

320
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:48,730
<i>Dangerous Liaisons</i>.

321
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:50,450
Correct, "Her actual favorite movie is...?"

322
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,560
<i>Weekend at Bernie's</i>.

323
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,720
"Monica categorizes her towels.

324
00:13:55,770 --> 00:13:57,890
How many categories are there?"

325
00:13:57,940 --> 00:13:59,370
- Everyday use. - Fancy.

326
00:13:59,420 --> 00:14:01,020
- Guest. - Fancy guest.

327
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:03,150
- Two seconds. - Eleven?

328
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:06,480
Eleven! Unbelievable! Eleven is correct.

329
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,700
"Chandler was how old

330
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,360
when he first touched a girl's breast?"

331
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:12,820
- 14? - No, 19.

332
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:13,890
Thanks, man.

333
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:17,400
"Joey had an imaginary childhood friend.

334
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,760
- His name was...?" - Maurice!

335
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,210
Correct! "His profession was...?"

336
00:14:20,210 --> 00:14:21,620
Space cowboy!

337
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:25,040
"What is Chandler Bing's job?"

338
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:31,330
Ten seconds.

339
00:14:31,330 --> 00:14:32,520
You need this or you lose.

340
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,390
Something to do with transponding.

341
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:38,180
He's a transpons...transponster!

342
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,190
That's not even a word!

343
00:14:51,630 --> 00:14:54,310
You are mean boys

344
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,560
who are just being mean!

345
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,180
Don't get mad!

346
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:59,070
No one forced you to raise the stakes.

347
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,860
That is not true! She forced me!

348
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:03,100
Hey, we would still be living here

349
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:04,460
if you hadn't gotten the question wrong!

350
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:07,040
It was a stupid, unfair question!

351
00:15:07,090 --> 00:15:08,800
Don't blame the questions!

352
00:15:08,930 --> 00:15:11,300
Stop yelling in our apartment!

353
00:15:11,350 --> 00:15:13,660
You are ruining moving day for us.

354
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:16,070
Chandler!

355
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:22,140
I saw what you were doing in the window!

356
00:15:22,190 --> 00:15:24,220
I saw what you're doing to my sister!

357
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:25,550
Get out here!

358
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:28,540
Listen, we had a good run.

359
00:15:29,150 --> 00:15:31,280
What was it? Four, five months?

360
00:15:31,330 --> 00:15:32,330
I mean that's more

361
00:15:32,380 --> 00:15:33,570
than most people have in a lifetime.

362
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:34,980
So, goodbye, take care, byebye.

363
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:37,970
Hey, Ross.

364
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:38,850
What's up, bro?

365
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:45,350
What the hell are you doing?

366
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,450
What's going on?

367
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:50,250
I think...I think Ross knows about me and Monica.

368
00:15:51,810 --> 00:15:53,880
Dude, he's right there.

369
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,870
I thought you were my best friend!

370
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,470
This is my sister!

371
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,180
My best friend and my sister!

372
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:02,830
I cannot believe this!

373
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,990
We're not just messing around.

374
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:06,340
I love her.

375
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:08,500
I'm in love with her.

376
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:10,740
I'm so sorry

377
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,290
that you had to find out this way.

378
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:15,190
I'm sorry, but it's true.

379
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,480
I love him too.

380
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:26,130
My best friend and my sister!

381
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:31,160
I cannot believe this!

382
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:34,390
This is the last box of your clothes.

383
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,770
I'm just gonna label it

384
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:37,220
"What were you thinking?"

385
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:41,200
I was gonna go across the hall

386
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,810
and write that on Chandler.

387
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:48,170
Guys, I don't mean to make things worse, but...

388
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:50,470
...l don't want to live with Rachel anymore.

389
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:51,340
-What? -What?

390
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:53,440
You're so mean to each other.

391
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:55,560
I don't wanna end up like that with Rachel.

392
00:16:55,610 --> 00:16:56,860
I still like you.

393
00:16:57,380 --> 00:16:59,860
That's fine because I'm not moving.

394
00:17:01,030 --> 00:17:02,530
Phoebe, you gotta take her.

395
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,670
You know, I know I said some bad stuff...

396
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,990
...but Rachel has qualities

397
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,150
that make her a good roommate.

398
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,330
She gets tons of catalogs and she folds

399
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:14,040
she folds down the pages of things she thinks I'd like.

400
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:15,570
What else?

401
00:17:17,470 --> 00:17:18,850
When I take a shower...

402
00:17:19,650 --> 00:17:21,520
...she leaves me notes on the mirror.

403
00:17:21,860 --> 00:17:23,620
I do. I do do that.

404
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,680
That's nice.

405
00:17:26,020 --> 00:17:28,020
I like having things to read in the bathroom.

406
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:33,210
When I fall asleep on the couch...

407
00:17:34,380 --> 00:17:36,080
...she covers me with a blanket.

408
00:17:36,690 --> 00:17:40,200
Well, you know, I don't want you to be cold.

409
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:44,540
And when I told her

410
00:17:44,590 --> 00:17:46,290
that I was gonna move in with Chandler...

411
00:17:47,660 --> 00:17:49,590
...she was really supportive.

412
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,950
You were so great.

413
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:57,840
You made it so easy.

414
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,250
And now you have to leave.

415
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:04,830
And I have to live with a boy!

416
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,810
- She really left. - I know.

417
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,600
- Thank you. - No problem, roomie.

418
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:40,290
- Can I ask you a question? - Sure.

419
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,700
What the hell is that dog doing here?

420
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:46,390
A little toast here. Ding, ding!

421
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:48,330
I know this isn't exactly

422
00:18:48,380 --> 00:18:50,240
the kind of Thanksgiving you planned...

423
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:53,800
...but for me this has been really great.

424
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:55,860
You know, I think because

425
00:18:55,910 --> 00:18:57,890
it didn't involve divorce...

426
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:59,320
...or projectile vomiting.

427
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:02,960
Anyway, I think if

428
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:03,900
you had gone to Vail...

429
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:06,040
...or if you had been with your family,

430
00:19:06,090 --> 00:19:07,470
or if you didn't have...

431
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:10,020
...syphilis and stuff...

432
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:14,360
...we wouldn't be all together.

433
00:19:14,410 --> 00:19:16,640
So I guess what I'm trying to say is...

434
00:19:16,690 --> 00:19:18,810
...that I'm very thankful

435
00:19:18,860 --> 00:19:21,610
that all of your Thanksgivings sucked.

436
00:19:23,050 --> 00:19:26,070
- That's so sweet! - Thank you.

437
00:19:28,620 --> 00:19:30,800
Here's to a lousy Christmas!

438
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:32,410
And a crappy New Year!

439
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:34,460
Hear, hear!

440
00:19:40,730 --> 00:19:41,770
You can't move.

441
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:43,000
You just-- You just can't.

442
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:43,840
Rachel's right.

443
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:45,710
This is where you guys belong.

444
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,570
Yeah.You don't wanna live in Westchester.

445
00:19:47,620 --> 00:19:49,370
That's the worst of the Chesters.

446
00:19:50,810 --> 00:19:51,490
You know,

447
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:53,320
sometimes when I'm alone in my apartment,

448
00:19:53,370 --> 00:19:54,300
I look over here...

449
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:57,710
...and you guys are just having dinner...

450
00:19:58,190 --> 00:20:00,520
...or watching TV or something...

451
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:03,330
...but it makes me feel better.

452
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:04,510
And now when I look over,

453
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:05,960
who am I gonna see?

454
00:20:06,010 --> 00:20:08,360
The Gottliebs? The Yangs?

455
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:11,580
They don't make me feel so good.

456
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:15,430
Yeah. So don't move, okay?

457
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,930
Just stay here...

458
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:18,980
...and maybe close your blinds at night.

459
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:19,560
Hey.

460
00:20:25,970 --> 00:20:26,950
Hello?

461
00:20:30,420 --> 00:20:32,710
It's Nancy. They responded to our offer.

462
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:33,750
And?

463
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,240
Okay. Thanks.

464
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,030
They passed.

465
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:46,580
They said they won't go a penny under the asking price.

466
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:49,050
- We can't afford that. - I know.

467
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,220
Well, there you go.

468
00:20:58,140 --> 00:20:59,680
I'm really sorry, you guys.

469
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:01,750
Yeah, I'm sorry too.

470
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:04,400
I'm even more sorry that phone call didn't come...

471
00:21:04,450 --> 00:21:06,340
...before I told you about looking through the window.

472
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:09,950
Yeah. Well, we're gonna let you be alone.

473
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:10,960
You gonna be okay?

474
00:21:11,010 --> 00:21:12,030
Yeah, we'll be okay.

475
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:13,220
Love you guys.

476
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,570
You know, I'm really sorry

477
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:19,220
I wasn't more supportive before.

478
00:21:19,270 --> 00:21:19,850
That's okay.

479
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:20,690
We understand.

480
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:22,660
Yeah, and about this Nancy....

481
00:21:22,710 --> 00:21:24,550
If you're not sleeping with her, should l?

482
00:21:31,770 --> 00:21:34,360
I know there'll be other houses, but I just--

483
00:21:34,410 --> 00:21:36,850
- I love that one so much. - Yeah.

484
00:21:38,270 --> 00:21:40,140
Well, it's a good thing we got it then.

485
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,150
- What? - We got the house.

486
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:46,000
Oh, my God.

487
00:21:46,050 --> 00:21:47,770
I didn't wanna tell you in front of them.

488
00:21:47,820 --> 00:21:49,560
Oh my god, we got it?! We got the house?!

489
00:21:49,610 --> 00:21:50,970
We're getting a house!

490
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,250
- We're getting a house. - And a baby.

491
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,600
We're growing up.

492
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,660
We sure are.

493
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:04,990
- Who's gonna tell them? - Not it!

494
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,620
Not it! Damn it!

495
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:13,140
Rachel, this is yours.

496
00:22:13,730 --> 00:22:15,600
Why? What are these for?

497
00:22:15,650 --> 00:22:16,580
You'll see.

498
00:22:16,630 --> 00:22:18,430
All right, everybody open them.

499
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:23,260
Wow, this is so beautiful!

500
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:26,250
These are the ones I was looking at in the store!

501
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:28,330
- I know. - Oh, I love this!

502
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:30,080
A meatball sub!

503
00:22:30,970 --> 00:22:32,210
Thanks!

504
00:22:32,260 --> 00:22:34,040
Seriously, guys, what's going on?

505
00:22:34,090 --> 00:22:35,160
What are these for?

506
00:22:35,210 --> 00:22:37,890
Well, I didn't know how to tell you before...

507
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,610
- ...but we got the house. - Enjoy!

508
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,050
What did they say?

